In a network with n genes, a set of binary variables V={X1,X2,…,Xn}, Xi∈{0,1}, determines the expression states of the genes. The vector of gene expression values at time t, X(t)=(X1(t),…,Xn(t)), referred to as the gene activity profile (GAP), defines the network state at each time step. In a Markovian regulatory network, network dynamics involves a trajectory of states over time governed by the transition rule X(t+1)=f(X(t),w(t)), t≥0, where w(t)∈Ξ captures randomness in the system and \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
