In the first set of simulations, we generate 100 synthetic BNps. After extracting corresponding conditional probabilities for each network, we randomly select 5 conditional probabilities in each network and assume they are unknown. The aim is to decide which unknown conditional probability should be determined first. For each network, we generate a state trajectory \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
